      <byline class="print_byline">By Peter Valdina</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Valdina, Peter</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Polytechnic University introduces bachelor of science degree in construction management; Dr Bud Griffis comments; photo (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Polytechnic University in Brooklyn is introducing a new bachelor of science degree in construction management beginning this fall, one of the first such undergraduate programs in the Northeast. The program includes training in computer applications, economics and management related to construction. Dr. BUD GRIFFIS, head of the department of civil engineering and developer of the new degree, said that construction had become increasingly complicated by litigation and technology and that more managers need specialized undergraduate training.</p>
        <p>Peter Valdina</p>
      </block>
